  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    arrayStore
    The arrayStore class is used to store the Array size and time taken for the array to be sorted, using different instances of the class to store the values and recording them in an ArrayList
    bubbleSort
    The bubbleSort class is is used to implement a Bubble Sorting process on an Array of random integers that are automatically generated by the algorithm, the class can be used to either animate the bubble sort process or record the time taken to fully sort a single array.
    Controller
    Controller class for the project, contains the main method that creates and runs mainForm using an anonymous inner class
    drawPanel
    The drawPanel class is a JPanel, this class operates as the drawing window for the application.
    mainForm
    This class is the programs top level container and contains all the swing elements for interacting with the program along with action listeners and methods to handle these interactions
